MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Implements a fiber architecture for GPUI that replaces the arena-based
per-frame element tree rebuilding with a persistent fiber structure.
This reduces layout/render complexity from O(total elements) to
O(changed elements) per frame.

Key changes:
- Add fiber.rs with FiberTree, FiberNode, and reconciliation logic
- Add identity.rs for stable element identity tracking
- Add render_node.rs for decoupled render tree
- Add transform.rs for cached transform propagation
- Add virtualized_list.rs for efficient large list rendering
- Remove arena.rs and bounds_tree.rs (no longer needed)
- Update window.rs and all element implementations for fiber API
